\mt1 Leviticus
\is1 Introduction
\ip The Latin word \bk Leviticus\bk* means вҖҳconcerning the LevitesвҖҷ, who were the tribe of workers and priests who God chose serve him at the altar and in other religious ceremonies. Hebrew readers call this document вҖҳVayikrДҒвҖҷ which is the first word in the Hebrew and means вҖҳAnd he calledвҖҷ (Yahweh called Mosheh). Some European and other translations call it вҖҳThe third book of Mosheh/MosesвҖҷ.
\ip It's believed that of people Moses just the writer of this book there to Mountain Sinai at time of camped them there, because can be read this there to: 1:1, 4:1, 6:1,24, and of 8:1.
\ip The Libitiku document concerning this of correct behaviour of descendants of Yisrael/Israel so that eg-isipen them clean of God. The one means eg-isipen them clean of God is the sacrificing of desire of God.
\ip And/Now so that egkaay-ayaran indeed the sacrificing, mig-alam the god of person Aharon/Aaron and his descendants.
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The laws concerning the offerings and of sacrifices \ior 1:1вҖ“7:38\ior*
\io1 The dedication of Aharon and of his children males so that to become priests \ior 8:1вҖ“10:20\ior*
\io1 The laws concerning the cleaning and of not clean \ior 11:1вҖ“15:33\ior*
\io1 The day of forgiveness of sin \ior 16:1-34\ior*
\io1 The laws concerning the pegpabecome_holy of birth and of worshipping \ior 17:1вҖ“27:34\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Procedures for burnt sacrifices
\rem /s1 Sacrifices Burned Whole; The Burnt Offering; Offerings and sacrifices; Procedures for the Burnt Offering
\p
\v 1 YahwehВҰ46173 \add вүҲsummoned\add* MoshehВҰ46171 \add (MosesВҰ46171)\add* to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46175\add* tent andВҰ46172 \add вүҲtold him\add*,
\v 2 вҖңTellВҰ46183 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ46182\add* that when anyoneВҰ46186 presents an offeringВҰ46205 to YahwehВҰ46192, it must be presented from their \add ?own\add* herd or flockВҰ46201.
\v 3 If it's from the herd, it must be a bull with noВҰ46215 defectsВҰ46215. It must be presentedВҰ46223 \add вүҲin frontВҰ46226 of\add* the entranceВҰ46219 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46221\add* tent to be acceptableВҰ46225 to YahwehВҰ46227.
\v 4 \add @The owner\add* must place his handВҰ46230 on the headВҰ46232 of that offeringВҰ46233 to be burntВҰ46233, andВҰ46229 thenВҰ46229 it will be acceptedВҰ46234 \add вүҲmake him right with Yahweh\add*.
\v 5 ThenВҰ46239 he must slaughterВҰ46239 the \add вүҲbull in frontВҰ46244\add* of YahwehВҰ46245, and the priestsВҰ46249 (Aharon's \add (Aaron'sВҰ46248)\add* descendants), must presentВҰ46246 the blood and splash it all aroundВҰ46260 the altarВҰ46259 whichВҰ46261 is by the entranceВҰ46263 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46264\add* tent.
\v 6 ThenВҰ46267 \add @the presenter\add* must skin the \add вүҲbull\add* andВҰ46271 cut it into piecesВҰ46273,
\v 7 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the priestВҰ46278 Aharon's sons must put fire on the altarВҰ46282 andВҰ46275 arrangeВҰ46283 wood on the fire,
\v 8 and thenВҰ46289 \add *they\add* must arrangeВҰ46289 the piecesВҰ46294 (includingВҰ46298 the headВҰ46297 and the fat portions) on top of the burningВҰ46307 wood on the altarВҰ46311.
\v 9 ThenВҰ46313 \add @the presenter\add* must wash the innards and the feet withВҰ46316 waterВҰ46316, and the priestВҰ46318 must \add place it\add* onВҰ46316 the altarВҰ46322, \add вүҲensuring that everyВҰ46321 part is completely burntВҰ46323 up\add* as a pleasingВҰ46327 aromaВҰ46325 for YahwehВҰ46328.
\p
\v 10 вҖңIf the offeringВҰ46344 is from the flockВҰ46335 (i.e., a sheepВҰ46339 or a goat), then itВҰ46347 must be a healthy maleВҰ46345 that's presentedВҰ46347,
\v 11 and thenВҰ46349 it must be slaughteredВҰ46349 on the northernВҰ46354 side of the altar facing YahwehВҰ46356, and Aharon'sВҰ46359 sonsВҰ46358, the priestsВҰ46360, must splash itsВҰ46363 bloodВҰ46363 on the altar, all aroundВҰ46367.
\v 12 ThenВҰ46369 \add @the presenter\add* must cut it into piecesВҰ46371 and they must arrangeВҰ46378 them (includingВҰ46372 the headВҰ46374 and fat portions) on top of the burningВҰ46387 wood on the altarВҰ46391.
\v 13 ThenВҰ46393 \add @the presenterВҰ46397\add* must wash the innards and the feet withВҰ46396 waterВҰ46396, and the priestВҰ46398 must \add place itВҰ46405\add* onВҰ46396 the altarВҰ46403, \add вүҲensuring that everyВҰ46401 part is completely burntВҰ46404 up\add* as a pleasingВҰ46408 aromaВҰ46407 for YahwehВҰ46409.
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲHowever,\add* if his burntВҰ46416 offeringВҰ46416 to YahwehВҰ46418 will be a bird, then \add вүҲit must be either a doveВҰ46427 or a youngВҰ46426 pigeonВҰ46427\add*.
\v 15 The priestВҰ46433 must presentВҰ46432 it at the altar, and thenВҰ46432 twist its head off and burnВҰ46441 the head on the altar \add вүҲas he\add* drainsВҰ46443 the bloodВҰ46444 out onto the \add вүҲouter edge\add* of the altar.
\v 16 ThenВҰ46449 he must \add вүҲpull out\add* the crop withВҰ46453 its contentsВҰ46453, andВҰ46449 throwВҰ46454 it down onВҰ46453 the easternВҰ46458 side of the altarВҰ46457 where the ashesВҰ46462 are.
\v 17 He will thenВҰ46464 tear the bird \add mostly\add* apartВҰ46464 by its wingsВҰ46466 \add вүҲ(butВҰ46464 making sure that it stays as one piece)\add*, andВҰ46464 \add place it\add* onВҰ46466 the altarВҰ46472, \add вүҲensuring that every part is completely burntВҰ46480 up\add* as a pleasingВҰ46484 aromaВҰ46483 for YahwehВҰ46485.
\c 2
\s1 Procedures for grain offerings
\rem /s1 Procedures for the Grain Offering; The Grain Offering; Grain Offerings
\p
\v 1 вҖңWhen someone presents a grainВҰ46493 offeringВҰ46493 to YahwehВҰ46494, it must be as fine, wheat flourВҰ46495 \add вүҲmixed with\add* \add olive\add*, and with frankincenseВҰ46503 added to the top of it.
\v 2 It must be taken to the priestВҰ46510 Aharon's sonsВҰ46508 who will take it \add from them\add*, thenВҰ46505 take a handfulВҰ46514 out, being sure to get flourВҰ46515, oilВҰ46516, and some frankincenseВҰ46520, and \add вүҲthrow that memorialВҰ46525 portionВҰ46525 onto\add* the altarВҰ46526 to get completely burnt up as a pleasingВҰ46529 aromaВҰ46528 for YahwehВҰ46530.
\v 3 ThenВҰ46532 the rest of that grainВҰ46535 offeringВҰ46535 will be for AharonВҰ46536 andВҰ46537 his sonsВҰ46537вҖ”it's a very sacredВҰ46538 part from the gifts for YahwehВҰ46541.
\p
\v 4 вҖңWhen someone presents something baked as their grainВҰ46547 offeringВҰ46547, it must be baked without leaven: either wheat flour mixedВҰ46553 with \add olive\add* oil and baked into flat buns, or else wheat flour biscuitsВҰ46555 with \add olive\add* oil \add вүҲspread onВҰ46554 top\add*.
\v 5 Or if yourВҰ46567 grainВҰ46563 offeringВҰ46563 is done onВҰ46570 the flat pan, itВҰ46572 must be wheat flourВҰ46568 mixedВҰ46569 withВҰ46570 \add olive\add* oilВҰ46570 \add вүҲandВҰ46561 made into flat biscuits\add*
\v 6 that should then be crumbledВҰ46574 andВҰ46577 have oilВҰ46579 poured over them as \add &your\add* grainВҰ46580 offeringВҰ46580.
\v 7 Or if yourВҰ46588 grainВҰ46586 offeringВҰ46586 is \add deep-fried\add* inВҰ46590 a pot, itВҰ46591 must be made from wheat flourВҰ46589 withВҰ46590 \add olive\add* oilВҰ46590.
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add Any of the above types of\add* grainВҰ46596 offeringВҰ46596 to YahwehВҰ46600 must be presentedВҰ46601 to the priestВҰ46604, andВҰ46593 he will takeВҰ46605 it to the altarВҰ46608.
\v 9 ThenВҰ46610 he must \add take a handful\add* as a memorialВҰ46617 portionВҰ46617 to the altarВҰ46619 to get completely burnt up as a pleasingВҰ46622 aromaВҰ46621 for YahwehВҰ46623.
\v 10 ThenВҰ46625 the rest of that grainВҰ46628 offeringВҰ46628 will be for AharonВҰ46629 andВҰ46630 his sonsВҰ46630вҖ”it's a very sacredВҰ46631 part from the gifts for YahwehВҰ46634.
\p
\v 11 вҖңAnything that's presentedВҰ46640 to Yahweh as a grainВҰ46638 offering must not be made with any rising agent, because any leaven or honeyВҰ46651 mustn't be burnt as a gift to Yahweh.
\v 12 \add вүҲFoodsВҰ46663 containing those\add* can be presented as a first-fruits offering, butВҰ46664 theyВҰ46669 mustn't \add вүҲbe burnt\add* on the altarВҰ46666.
\v 13 \add вүҲHowever,\add* everyВҰ46687 grain offering must be saltedвҖ”the salt inВҰ46677 the grain offering is a reminder of our agreement, \add вүҲso it must always be present\add*.
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲFinally,\add* if you want to offer ripe grain as a grain offering to YahwehВҰ46699, then it must be a youngВҰ46700 ear of grain that's been roastedВҰ46701 over the fireВҰ46702 and presented as a grain offering of your firstВҰ46698 ripe grains
\v 15 \add вүҲwith\add* \add olive\add* oilВҰ46712 on itВҰ46717 andВҰ46713 some frankincenseВҰ46715 on top. That \add also becomes\add* a grainВҰ46716 offeringВҰ46716,
\v 16 and the priestВҰ46720 must burnВҰ46719 a memorialВҰ46723 prtion from it with some of the crushedВҰ46724 grainsВҰ46724 and some of the oilВҰ46725 and some of the incense, \add to be burnt\add* to become smokeВҰ46719 as a gift to YahwehВҰ46731.
\c 3
\s1 Procedures for peace offerings
\rem /s1 The Fellowship Offering; Fellowship Offerings; Offerings of Well-Being; Procedures for the Peace Offering
\p
\v 1 вҖң\add вүҲNow\add* if it's a sacrificeВҰ46736 for a peaceВҰ46737 offeringВҰ46737, if it's fron the \bd herd\bd*, then either a male or femaleВҰ46750 can be presentedВҰ46744 to YahwehВҰ46754 \add вүҲas long as it has noВҰ46751 defectsВҰ46751\add*.
\v 2 \add @The presenterВҰ46761\add* must lay their handВҰ46757 on the headВҰ46760 of the \add вүҲbull or cow\add*, thenВҰ46756 he must slaughterВҰ46762 it \add вүҲin front of\add* the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46764\add* tent. ThenВҰ46756 the priestВҰ46769 Aharon'sВҰ46768 sonsВҰ46767 will splash the bloodВҰ46772 on the altarВҰ46775 \add вүҲon each side\add*.
\v 3 From thatВҰ46794 peaceВҰ46780 offeringВҰ46781, he must presentВҰ46778 the fat coveringВҰ46786 the innards andВҰ46778 whichВҰ46794 is part of the innards as a gift to YahwehВҰ46782,
\v 4 \add вүҲalong with bothВҰ46800\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ46816 (all of which need to be removedВҰ46820 \add from the animal\add*).
\v 5 ThenВҰ46822 Aharon'sВҰ46826 sonsВҰ46824 must burnВҰ46822 them on the wood \add вүҲthat's burningВҰ46838\add* on the altarВҰ46827 as a giftвҖ”to become smokeВҰ46822 as a pleasingВҰ46841 aromaВҰ46840 for YahwehВҰ46842.
\p
\v 6 вҖң\add вүҲHowever,\add* if the sacrificeВҰ46851 for a peaceВҰ46852 offeringВҰ46850 is from the \bd flockВҰ46849\bd*, then either a male or a femaleВҰ46856 can be presented to YahwehВҰ46853 \add вүҲas long as it has noВҰ46857 defectsВҰ46857\add*.
\v 7 When the offeringВҰ46868 is being presented, it must be presented \add вүҲin frontВҰ46871\add* of YahwehВҰ46872,
\v 8 and \add @the presenterВҰ46881\add* will put his handВҰ46877 on the headВҰ46880 of \add the animal being\add* offeredВҰ46881, and slaughterВҰ46882 it \add вүҲin frontВҰ46884\add* of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46885\add* tent. ThenВҰ46874 Aharon'sВҰ46889 sonsВҰ46888 must splash its bloodВҰ46892 on the altarВҰ46895, \add вүҲon each side\add*.
\v 9 From thatВҰ46908 peaceВҰ46900 offeringВҰ46901, he must presentВҰ46898 the fat as a gift to YahwehВҰ46902, \add вүҲalong with\add* the entireВҰ46917 fatty tail (cut off near the backboneВҰ46907), the fat coveringВҰ46912 the innards andВҰ46898 which is part of the innards,
\v 10 \add вүҲbothВҰ46926\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ46942 (all of which need to be removedВҰ46946 \add from the animal\add*).
\v 11 ThenВҰ46948 the priestВҰ46949 must burnВҰ46948 them on the altarВҰ46950 as a food offeringВҰ46952 made to YahwehВҰ46953 by fireВҰ46952.
\p
\v 12 вҖң\add вүҲSimilarly,\add* if the offeringВҰ46958 is a \bd goatВҰ46957\bd*, then itВҰ46959 can be presented to YahwehВҰ46961.
\v 13 \add @The presenter\add* will put his handВҰ46966 on its headВҰ46969, andВҰ46963 slaughterВҰ46970 it \add вүҲin frontВҰ46972\add* of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ46973\add* tent. ThenВҰ46963 Aharon'sВҰ46977 sonsВҰ46976 must splash its bloodВҰ46980 on the altarВҰ46983, \add вүҲon each side\add*.
\v 14 From thatВҰ47002 peace offeringВҰ46989, he must presentВҰ46986 the fat as a gift to YahwehВҰ46990, \add вүҲalong with\add* the fat coveringВҰ46994 the innards andВҰ46986 whichВҰ47002 is part of the innards,
\v 15 \add вүҲbothВҰ47008\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ47024 (all of which need to be removedВҰ47028 \add from the animal\add*).
\v 16 ThenВҰ47030 the priestВҰ47031 must burnВҰ47030 them on the altarВҰ47032 as a food offeringВҰ47034 made to Yahweh by fireВҰ47034 as a pleasingВҰ47036 aromaВҰ47035. All the fat \add вүҲbelongs to\add* Yahweh.
\p
\v 17 вҖң\add This\add* regulationВҰ47042 must be permanent for \add all\add* \add вүҲfuture\add* generationsВҰ47044: All of you must \add вүҲnever\add* eatВҰ47054 fat or bloodВҰ47052.вҖқ
\c 4
\s1 Procedures for sin offerings
\rem /s1 Procedures for the Sin Offering; Offerings for Unintentional Sins; Sin Offerings; The Sin Offering
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ47058 told MoshehВҰ47061 \add (MosesВҰ47061)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ47067\add* that if a person \add вүҲbreaks\add* any of Yahweh's regulations unintentionallyВҰ47075, or does anything that he said shouldn'tВҰ47080 be done, \add then this is the procedure:\add*
\p
\v 3 вҖңIf it's \bd the \+add вүҲhigh\+add* priestВҰ47087\bd* \add вүҲwho's done it\add*, \add thatВҰ47095 causes\add* the \add вүҲnation\add* to be guiltyВҰ47090, and for hisВҰ47094 transgression he must presentВҰ47092 a bullВҰ47097 \add вүҲwith noВҰ47101 defectsВҰ47101\add* to YahwehВҰ47102 as a sin offeringВҰ47092.
\v 4 He must bringВҰ47105 the bull before Yahweh at the entranceВҰ47111 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ47112\add* tent, thenВҰ47105 he must place his hand on \add *its\add* head andВҰ47105 slaughterВҰ47124 \add *it\add* \add вүҲin frontВҰ47114\add* of Yahweh.
\v 5 ThenВҰ47131 the \add вүҲhigh\add* priestВҰ47132 must get some of the bull'sВҰ47135 bloodВҰ47134 andВҰ47131 bringingВҰ47136 it into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ47140\add* tent,
\v 6 he must dip his fingerВҰ47147 into \add *it\add* andВҰ47143 sevenВҰ47153 timesВҰ47154 he must \add вүҲflick\add* the blood \add вүҲtowards\add* the \add вүҲfront\add* of the curtainВҰ47160 of the sanctuaryВҰ47161 \add вүҲinВҰ47148 front\add* of YahwehВҰ47156.
\v 7 Then the \add high\add* priestВҰ47164 must put some of the blood onВҰ47177 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the incense altar (\add вүҲlocated\add* inside the sacred tent \add вүҲinВҰ47177 frontВҰ47174\add* of YahwehВҰ47175 \add and\add* used for \add burning\add* fragrantВҰ47173 incense). Then \add he must go back outside and\add* pour \add вүҲthe rest\add* of the bull'sВҰ47184 blood out at the base of the altar for burntВҰ47190 offeringsВҰ47190 (which is \add out\add* at the entranceВҰ47193 to the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent).
\v 8 ThenВҰ47197 \add @the high priest\add* must \add вүҲremove\add* all the fat from the bullВҰ47202 being offered as a sinВҰ47203 offering, \add includingВҰ47213\add* the fat coveringВҰ47209 the innards andВҰ47213 whichВҰ47217 is a part of the innards,
\v 9 \add вүҲbothВҰ47223\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ47239 (all of which need to be removedВҰ47243 \add from the animal\add*)
\v 10 just \add вүҲlike you'd do\add* for the bullВҰ47247 of the peaceВҰ47249 offering. Then the priestВҰ47251 must burnВҰ47250 them on the altarВҰ47253 for the burntВҰ47254 offering.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the bull's hide and its meatВҰ47264, plusВҰ47260 it's headВҰ47267 and feet, and innards and dung,
\v 12 must be taken outsideВҰ47282 the camp to the clean placeВҰ47286 where they pour out the ashes, and they must \add make\add* a fireВҰ47297 withВҰ47297 wood there onВҰ47297 top of the ashes and burnВҰ47292 it there.
\p
\v 13 вҖңIfВҰ47309 it's the \bd whole community\bd* that \add unintentionally\add* transgresses by doing something that YahwehВҰ47320 prohibited, then they'll be guiltyВҰ47325 even if the community didn'tВҰ47322 \add actually\add* noticeВҰ47313.\x + \xo 4:13-21: \xt Num 15:22-26.\x*
\v 14 \add вүҲWhenВҰ47327\add* they become aware of \add вүҲwhat they've done wrong\add*, thenВҰ47327 the community must presentВҰ47332 a \add вүҲyoungВҰ47335\add* bullВҰ47334 \add вүҲin frontВҰ47341\add* of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ47342\add* tent as a sin offeringВҰ47332.
\v 15 ThenВҰ47345 the communityВҰ47347 eldersВҰ47346 must place theirВҰ47350 handsВҰ47350 of the bull'sВҰ47354 headВҰ47353 \add вүҲin frontВҰ47355\add* of YahwehВҰ47356, andВҰ47357 slaughterВҰ47357 \add *it there\add*.
\v 16 The \add вүҲhigh\add* priestВҰ47365 must take some of the bull'sВҰ47368 bloodВҰ47367 into the \add вүҲsacredВҰ47371\add* tent
\v 17 and sevenВҰ47381 timesВҰ47382 \add *he\add* must dip his fingerВҰ47376 in it and \add вүҲflick\add* the bloodВҰ47379 \add вүҲtowards\add* the \add вүҲfront\add* of the curtainВҰ47387 of the sanctuary \add вүҲin front\add* of YahwehВҰ47384.
\v 18 Then he must put some of the blood onВҰ47402 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the \add incense\add* altar (\add вүҲlocated\add* inside the sacred tent \add вүҲinВҰ47402 frontВҰ47399\add* of YahwehВҰ47400). Then \add he must go back outside andВҰ47389\add* pour \add вүҲthe rest of\add* the bull's blood out at the base of the altar for burntВҰ47413 offeringsВҰ47413 (which is \add out\add* at the entranceВҰ47416 to the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent).
\v 19 ThenВҰ47420 he must \add вүҲremove\add* all the fat from \add @the slaughtered bull\add* andВҰ47420 burnВҰ47426 up \add @that fat\add* on the altarВҰ47427,
\v 20 and he should process the bull just the same as for a sin offeringВҰ47434. ThenВҰ47429 the priestВҰ47441 \add вүҲwill have made them right with God\add* and they'll be forgivenВҰ47442.
\v 21 ThenВҰ47445 he must take \add the remaining parts of\add* the bull outsideВҰ47451 the camp and burn it \add вүҲas described above\add* \add and\add* it will be the sin offeringВҰ47460 for the community.
\p
\v 22 вҖңIf it's \bd a leaderВҰ47466\bd* that \add unintentionallyВҰ47479\add* transgresses by doing something that his godВҰ47474 YahwehВҰ47473 prohibited, then he'll be guiltyВҰ47480.
\v 23 \add Alternatively, maybe someone else will point out his failing\add* to him. Then he must bringВҰ47490 an offeringВҰ47493 of a male goatВҰ47494 \add вүҲwithВҰ47489 noВҰ47497 defectsВҰ47497\add*.
\v 24 He must place his handВҰ47500 onВҰ47507 \add *its\add* headВҰ47503 andВҰ47499 slaughter it inВҰ47507 the place whereВҰ47508 \add the animals for\add* the burntВҰ47513 offering are slaughtered. It will be a sin offering,
\v 25 and the priestВҰ47520 must take some of the blood of that sin offering and withВҰ47523 his fingerВҰ47523, put some of the blood onВҰ47523 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar for burnt offerings.
\v 26 He must burn up all the fat on the altarВҰ47546 just like the fat from the peaceВҰ47549 offeringВҰ47549, and \add that way\add*, the priestВҰ47552 will make \add @that leader\add* \add вүҲright with God\add* and he'll be forgivenВҰ47554.
\p
\v 27 вҖңIf it's \bd an \+add ordinary\+add* personВҰ47560\bd* who \add unintentionallyВҰ47563\add* transgresses by doingВҰ47566 something thatВҰ47570 YahwehВҰ47569 prohibited, then they'll be guiltyВҰ47574.\x + \xo 4:27-31: \xt Num 15:27-28.\x*
\v 28 \add Alternatively, maybe someone else will point out their failing\add* to them. Then due to their transgression, \add @that person\add* must bringВҰ47582 an offeringВҰ47583 of a female goatВҰ47584 \add вүҲwith noВҰ47586 defectsВҰ47586\add*.
\v 29 He must place his handВҰ47597 onВҰ47605 the headВҰ47599 of the \add goat that's a\add* sin offering, andВҰ47594 slaughterВҰ47601 \add *it\add* atВҰ47605 the place for burntВҰ47606 offerings.
\v 30 ThenВҰ47608 the priestВҰ47609 must take some of the blood \add and\add* withВҰ47611 his fingerВҰ47611, put some of the blood onВҰ47611 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar for burntВҰ47617 offeringsВҰ47617, and thenВҰ47608 pour \add the rest of\add* the blood atВҰ47611 the altar's base.
\v 31 ThenВҰ47629 \add @the presenter\add* must pull out all the fat (just like it's done for the peaceВҰ47640 offeringВҰ47640), and the priest will \add вүҲburnВҰ47641\add* it on the altarВҰ47643 to make a pleasingВҰ47645 aromaВҰ47644 for YahwehВҰ47646, and to \add вүҲmake that person right with God\add*, and they'll be forgivenВҰ47650.
\p
\v 32 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ47654\add* if it's a lamb that \add @the individual\add* wants to bring as their sinВҰ47659 offeringВҰ47659, then it must be a femaleВҰ47660 \add вүҲwith noВҰ47661 defectsВҰ47661\add*.
\v 33 \add @The presenter\add* must put their handВҰ47667 onВҰ47674 the headВҰ47669 of the \add вүҲlamb\add* andВҰ47664 slaughter it as a sin offering atВҰ47674 the placeВҰ47674 whereВҰ47675 burntВҰ47679 offerings are slaughtered.
\v 34 ThenВҰ47681 the priestВҰ47682 must take some of the blood \add and\add* withВҰ47685 his fingerВҰ47685, put some of the blood onВҰ47685 the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar for burntВҰ47691 offerings, and thenВҰ47681 pour \add the rest of\add* the blood atВҰ47685 the altar's base.
\v 35 ThenВҰ47703 \add @the presenter\add* must pull out all the fat (just like it's done for the peaceВҰ47715 offeringВҰ47721), and the priest will \add вүҲburnВҰ47716\add* it on the altarВҰ47719 to make a pleasing aroma for YahwehВҰ47722, and to \add вүҲmake thatВҰ47729 person right with God\add*, and they'll be forgivenВҰ47732.
\c 5
\s1 More needs for sin offerings
\rem /s1 Cases Requiring Sin Offerings; Sins Requiring a Sin Offering
\p
\v 1 вҖңIf someone is a witnessВҰ47744 to a case \add вүҲbecause of something they sawВҰ47746 or knewВҰ47748 about\add*, and hearsВҰ47740 an oath \add in court\add* butВҰ47736 doesn't \add вүҲtestify\add*, then they'll \add вүҲbecome guiltyВҰ47754\add*.
\p
\v 2 вҖңIf someone touchesВҰ47759 anything вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ (e.g., a dead domestic or wild animalВҰ47766, or some creature) \add вүҲwithout realising it\add*, they \add still\add* become вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ and is guiltyВҰ47781.
\p
\v 3 вҖңIf someone touchesВҰ47785 anything вҖҳuncleanВҰ47791вҖҷ from \add another\add* person, even if they \add initially\add* \add вүҲdidn't realise what it was\add*, they become guiltyВҰ47797.
\p
\v 4 вҖңIf someone makes a rash promise, whether it's to do something goodВҰ47808 or something bad, and even if they were \add just\add* speakingВҰ47811 carelessly butВҰ47814 find out \add later\add*, they become guiltyВҰ47819.
\p
\v 5 вҖң\add вүҲSoВҰ47823 thenВҰ47823\add* \add @the person\add* that became guiltyВҰ47826 from any of the above, must confessВҰ47829 their wrongdoing
\v 6 and present a penaltyВҰ47837 to YahwehВҰ47838 to address thatВҰ47841 wrongdoing, and must present a female lamb or young goatВҰ47850 as a sin offeringВҰ47852, and the priestВҰ47855 will \add act on their behalf\add* \add вүҲto make them right with God\add*.
\p
\v 7 вҖң\add вүҲHowever if thatВҰ47870 person can'tВҰ47860 afford\add* a sheepВҰ47865, thenВҰ47858 for their guiltВҰ47869 offering because of \add вүҲtheir transgression\add*, they must bringВҰ47866 two doves or \add вүҲyoungВҰ47877\add* pigeons to YahwehВҰ47880вҖ”one for a sinВҰ47882 offering andВҰ47858 one for a burntВҰ47884 offering.
\v 8 \add @The presenter\add* must take them to the priestВҰ47890 who will present the sinВҰ47895 offeringВҰ47891 firstВҰ47896вҖ”twisting \add @the bird's\add* headВҰ47900 off from the neck, \add вүҲbutВҰ47886\add* not \add вүҲpulling\add* the body \add in half\add*.
\v 9 ThenВҰ47906 he must sprinkleВҰ47906 some of the blood from that sin offering onto the side of the altar, andВҰ47906 thenВҰ47906 drainВҰ47915 out the rest of the blood atВҰ47914 the altar's base. That will be the sin offering.
\v 10 The secondВҰ47925 \add >bird\add* will be for a burntВҰ47927 offeringВҰ47926 as per the regulationВҰ47928. The priestВҰ47931 will make \add @the presenter\add* \add вүҲright with God\add* after their wrongdoing, andВҰ47923 they'll be forgivenВҰ47936.
\p
\v 11 вҖң\add вүҲHowever if thatВҰ47956 person still can'tВҰ47942 afford\add* those two doves or \add вүҲyoungВҰ47949\add* pigeons, then they can presentВҰ47955 a kilogram of fine wheat flourВҰ47960 for a sin offering. It mustn't have oilВҰ47966 or frankincenseВҰ47971 in it because it's a sin offering.
\v 12 \add @The presenter\add* must take it to the priest who will thenВҰ47976 take a handful of it, andВҰ47976 burnВҰ47989 that memorialВҰ47988 portionВҰ47988 on the altarВҰ47990 for burnt offerings to YahwehВҰ47993. That will be the sinВҰ47994 offering.
\v 13 The priest will make \add @the presenter\add* \add вүҲright with God\add* after their wrongdoing as per one of the above, andВҰ47997 they'll be forgivenВҰ48008. \add The rest of\add* \add @the flour\add* will be for the priest, similar to a grainВҰ48012 offeringВҰ48012.вҖқ
\s1 More on guilt offerings
\rem /s1 Repayment Offerings; The Guilt Offering; Procedures for the Guilt Offering; Offerings with Restitution
\p
\v 14 Then YahwehВҰ48016 told MoshehВҰ48019 \add (MosesВҰ48019)\add*,
\v 15 вҖңIfВҰ48035 someone acts unfaithfullyВҰ48025 \add вүҲbutВҰ48027\add* unintentionallyВҰ48028 \add вүҲdesecrates something that's sacredВҰ48029\add* to YahwehВҰ48030, then because of their guilt, \add @that person\add* must present ram \add вүҲwithВҰ48028 noВҰ48037 defectsВҰ48037\add* from the flockВҰ48040, or silverВҰ48042 \add вүҲcoins using the official valuationВҰ48041\add*, as a guilt offering.
\v 16 They must also compensate for the sacredВҰ48055 item, butВҰ48050 with an extra twenty percent. That must all be given to the priest who will make \add @the presenter\add* \add вүҲright with God\add* with thatВҰ48051 ram as the guiltВҰ48069 offeringВҰ48069, andВҰ48050 they'll be forgivenВҰ48070.
\p
\v 17 вҖңIf someone transgresses by violatingВҰ48079 \add even\add* one of Yahweh's \add вүҲregulations or prohibitions\add*, even if they didn'tВҰ48086 realise itВҰ48078, they become guilty and must bear responsibility for thatВҰ48085 guilt.
\v 18 ThenВҰ48095 \add @that person\add* must take a ram from the flockВҰ48100 that \add вүҲhas noВҰ48097 defectsВҰ48097\add* to the priest for a guiltВҰ48102 offeringВҰ48102. Then the priest will make \add @the presenter\add* \add вүҲright withВҰ48101 God\add* after that transgression (even if they weren't aware of it), andВҰ48095 they'll be forgivenВҰ48118.
\v 19 That's a guilt offeringВҰ48121, because they were clearly guilty before YahwehВҰ48125.вҖқ
\c 6
\rem /s1 Sins Requiring a Guilt Offering
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ48271 told MoshehВҰ48274 \add (MosesВҰ48274)\add*,\x + \xo 6:1-7: \xt Num 5:5-8.\x*
\v 2 вҖңSomeone who transgresses against Yahweh by \add вүҲcheating\add* with respect to a deposit or a pledge, or by theft or extortion,
\v 3 or by finding lost property and then denying itВҰ48324, or making an oath that was knowingly false, or by any other typical transgression that people do,
\v 4 then they've become guilty as a result of that transgression. \add @That person\add* must return what was stolen or extorted, or \add вүЎreturn\add* the deposit or the lost property,
\v 5 or \add вүҲmake amends for a false oath\add*. They must return the full value plusВҰ48358 an extra twenty percent \add вүҲas soon as the guilt is discovered\add*.
\v 6 Then \add @that person\add* must take a ram from the flock \add вүҲwith no defects\add* to the priest as a guilt offering to Yahweh,
\v 7 and the priest will make \add @the presenterВҰ48397\add* \add вүҲright with YahwehВҰ48403\add* after whatever that transgression was to make them guilty, and they'll be forgiven.
\s1 The fire and the ashes
\rem /s1 Further Instructions for the Burnt Offering; Sacrifices Burned Whole; The Burnt Offering; Instructions concerning Sacrifices
\p
\v 8 Then YahwehВҰ48429 told Mosheh,
\v 9 вҖңTell Aharon \add (AaronВҰ48435)\add* and his sonsВҰ48436 that these are the \add #regulations\add* for the burnt \add #offerings\add*: The burnt offering must remainВҰ48432 on the altar's hearth, on the altar all night until the morning and the fire \add вүҲmust be kept burning\add* on it.
\v 10 ThenВҰ48452 the priest must \add вүҲput on\add* his linen underwear and linen robe and \add вүҲremove\add* the fatty ashes from the burnt \add #offerings\add* on the altar, and pile them beside \add *it\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲAfter that\add*, he'll \add вүҲget changed again into his regular\add* clothes and take \add &those\add* ashes outside the camp to a вҖҳcleanвҖҷ place.
\v 12 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the fire on the altar must be kept burningвҖ”it must never go out. Every morning the priest must put more wood on the fire, then he must arrange more offerings on the fireвҖ”he should burn the fat of the fellowship offerings on that fire so the smoke rises.
\v 13 \add Yes,\add* the fire must burn continuallyВҰ48506 onВҰ48508 the altarвҖ”never going out.
\s1 Procedures for the grain offering
\rem /s1 Further Instructions for the Grain Offering; The Grain Offering; Grain Offerings
\p
\v 14 вҖңHere's the regulations for the grainВҰ48521 offeringВҰ48521: Aharon's sons must presentВҰ48523 it \add вүҲbefore\add* YahwehВҰ48527 \add вүҲinВҰ48516 front\add* of the altar.
\v 15 \add @The priestВҰ48530\add* must take a handful of the flour from that grain offeringВҰ48534, being sure it includes some of the oil and the incense, and burn it on the altar as a memorial portionВҰ48536 to become a pleasing aroma for YahwehВҰ48539.
\v 16 The remainder \add of that flour\add* will be \add вүҲused as food\add* for Aharon andВҰ48544 his sonsвҖ”they must eat the flat bread in a sacred place, i.e., in the courtyard of the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent.
\v 17 It must not be baked with any rising agent. I give that to them from \add вүҲwhat's given to me\add*. It's \add вүҲvery\add* sacred just like the sin offering andВҰ48555 the guilt offering.
\v 18 Any of Aharon's male descendants can eat itвҖ”it'll be their portion from Yahweh's gifts throughout the generations. Anyone who touches \add @Yahweh's gifts\add* will become sacredВҰ48582 \add themself\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Procedures for the ordination offering
\rem /s1 Procedures for the Ordination Offering
\p
\v 19 Then Yahweh told Mosheh,
\v 20 вҖңOn the day when one of Aharon's male descendants is consecrated as a priest, this is what he must present to Yahweh: a continual grain offering of a kilogram of fine wheat flourвҖ”half for the morning and half for the evening.
\v 21 It must be mixed with \add olive\add* oil then cooked with oil onВҰ48629 a flat pan. It must then be brokenВҰ48626 into pieces and presented as a grain offering to make a pleasing aroma for Yahweh.
\v 22 The priest who's next inВҰ48640 line to become \add вүҲhigh\add* priest must offer it and it must be completely burnt for Yahweh. This is a permanent regulation.
\v 23 Any grain offeringВҰ48650 by a priest must be completely burntвҖ”it must not be eatenВҰ48661.вҖқ
\s1 Procedures for the sin offering
\rem /s1 Sin Offerings; Further Instructions for the Sin Offering; The Sin Offering
\p
\v 24 Then Yahweh told Mosheh,
\v 25 вҖңTell Aharon and his sons that these are the \add #regulations\add* for the sin \add #offerings\add*: The sin offering must be slaughtered \add вүҲin front\add* of Yahweh at the place where the burnt \add #offerings\add* are slaughtered. It's a \add вүҲvery\add* sacred \add activity\add*.
\v 26 The priest who offers the sin offering \add вүҲmust be the one to eat it\add*. It must be eaten in a sacred place, i.e., in the courtyard of the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent.
\v 27 Everything that touches the \add animal's\add* body will become sacred. Anyone who \add вүҲgets the blood on their\add* clothes, must wash them in a sacred place.
\v 28 Any clay pot that it's been boiled in, must then be shattered, but if it's boiled in a bronze pot, then that must be scoured and rinsed with water.
\v 29 Any male in the priests' \add families\add* may eat itвҖ”it's \add вүҲvery\add* sacred.
\v 30 \add вүҲHowever,\add* every sin offering that has its blood taken inside the \add вүҲsacred\add* tent to make \add вүҲsomeone right with God\add*, then that \add meat\add* mustn't be eatenвҖ”it must be completely burnt up.
\c 7
\s1 Procedures for the guilt offering
\rem /s1 Repayment Offerings; The Guilt Offering; Further Instructions for the Guilt Offering
\p
\v 1 вҖңThen these are the \add #regulations\add* for the \add вүҲvery\add* sacredВҰ48669 guiltВҰ48668 \add #offerings\add*:
\v 2 The guiltВҰ48682 offering must be slaughtered at the same placeВҰ48673 as the burntВҰ48678 \add #offerings\add*, andВҰ48683 the bloodВҰ48685 must be splashed on \add вүҲeach side of\add* the altarВҰ48689.
\v 3 \add @The presenter\add* must present all the fat \add includingВҰ48700\add* the fatty tail, the fat coveringВҰ48703 the innards,
\v 4 \add вүҲbothВҰ48709\add* kidneys and the fat that's attached to them, and the lobe on the liverВҰ48725 (\add вүҲall of which\add* need to be removedВҰ48729 \add from the animal\add*).
\v 5 ThenВҰ48731 the priestВҰ48733 must burnВҰ48731 those on the altarВҰ48734 as a guiltВҰ48737 offering to YahwehВҰ48736.
\v 6 Any maleВҰ48742 inВҰ48743 the priests' \add families\add* may eatВҰ48744 itвҖ”it's \add вүҲvery\add* sacredВҰ48746.
\v 7 The regulations are the same for the guilt offering as for the sinВҰ48752 offeringвҖ”the priestВҰ48757 who \add вүҲoffers the guilt offering\add* \add вүҲmust be the one to eat it\add*.
\p
\v 8 вҖңWhenever a priest presents someone's burnt offering, the skin of the animal that was presented belongsВҰ48777 to that priest.
\v 9 Any grainВҰ48781 offeringВҰ48781 that's bakedВҰ48783 in an oven, or cooked in a pan or onВҰ48784 a griddle, will belongВҰ48796 to the priestВҰ48792 who presentsВҰ48793 it.
\v 10 Any grainВҰ48800 offeringВҰ48800 that's either dry or mixedВҰ48801 withВҰ48803 oilВҰ48803, belongsВҰ48809 to all of Aharon's male descendants \add вүҲwithout any distinction\add*.
\s1 Procedures for the peace offering
\rem /s1 The Fellowship Offering; Further Instructions; Fellowship Offerings; Further Instructions for the Peace Offering
\p
\v 11 вҖңThen these are the \add #regulations\add* for sacrificingВҰ48816 peaceВҰ48817 offeringsВҰ48817 to presentВҰ48819 to YahwehВҰ48820:
\v 12 If it's presented \add вүҲfrom thankfulness\add*, then the sacrificeВҰ48831 \add вүҲmust be accompanied by\add* thanksgiving flat bread buns (\add made from flour\add* mixed with \add olive\add* oil), and flat biscuitsВҰ48837 smearedВҰ48839 with oil, and buns \add made from\add* fine wheat flour mixed with oil,
\v 13 \add вүҲplus\add* risen breadВҰ48850 rolls. \add All that\add* must accompany the peaceВҰ48858 offeringВҰ48853 \add вүҲfrom thankfulnessВҰ48857\add*.
\v 14 ThenВҰ48860 he must present one of each \add kind of bread\add* as a contributionВҰ48866 to YahwehВҰ48867. Those will belongВҰ48875 to the priestВҰ48868 who splashes the bloodВҰ48872 for the peaceВҰ48873 offeringsВҰ48873.
\v 15 The meat of the thanksfulnessВҰ48879 sacrificeВҰ48878 of those peaceВҰ48880 offerings must be eatenВҰ48883 the \add вүҲsame dayВҰ48881 that it's offeredвҖ”none of can be left\add* untilВҰ48888 morningВҰ48890.
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if the sacrificed offering is a vow or freewillВҰ48897 offering, thenВҰ48892 it can be eaten that same day andВҰ48892 \add also\add* the next day,
\v 17 \add вүҲbutВҰ48911\add* any left-over meat must be burnt up on the fireВҰ48916 on the thirdВҰ48915 dayВҰ48914.
\v 18 If any of that meat from the sacrificeВҰ48924 was eaten on the thirdВҰ48927 dayВҰ48926, the presenterВҰ48930 won't be acceptedВҰ48929 and \add вүҲthey won't be forgiven\add*. It is spoilt, and anyoneВҰ48930 who eatsВҰ48938 any of it will bear their own \add вүҲguilt\add*.
\v 19 If any meat touchesВҰ48946 anything that's вҖҳuncleanВҰ48949вҖҷ, thenВҰ48943 it must not be eatenвҖ”it must be burnt up inВҰ48952 the fireВҰ48952. \add вүҲHowever,\add* any long as the meat remains вҖҳcleanвҖҷ, it can be eaten by any person who's вҖҳcleanвҖҷ.
\v 20 IfВҰ48969 a person who was вҖҳuncleanВҰ48970вҖҷ were to eat any of the meat from the sacrificeВҰ48966 for a peaceВҰ48967 offeringВҰ48967, thenВҰ48961 thatВҰ48968 \add >person\add* must be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲSimilarly,\add* when a person touchesВҰ48980 anything вҖҳuncleanвҖҷ (e.g., humanВҰ48985 uncleanness, or an unclean animalВҰ48988, or a detestableВҰ48993 creatureВҰ49003), andВҰ48977 thenВҰ48977 they eat some of the meat of the sacrificeВҰ48998 for a peaceВҰ48999 offeringВҰ48999 that \add now\add* belongs to YahwehВҰ49001, that \add >person\add* must be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.
\s1 Don't eat fat or blood
\rem /s1 Eating Fat and Blood Forbidden; The Forbidden Blood and Fat
\p
\v 22 Then YahwehВҰ49009 told MoshehВҰ49012,
\v 23 вҖңTellВҰ49019 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ49018\add* that you all must not eatВҰ49028 the fat from \add #cattle or sheepВҰ49025 or goats\add*,
\v 24 вҮ”plus you all definitely must not eat the fat from an animal \add вүҲthat died naturally or was killed by wild animals although you can use it for other purposes\add*.
\v 25 AnyoneВҰ49045 who does eat the fat from an animal presentedВҰ49051 as a gift to YahwehВҰ49054 must be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.
\p
\v 26 вҖң\add вүҲAlso,\add* you all must not eatВҰ49064 bloodВҰ49062 from either a bird or an animalВҰ49068, \add вүҲno matter where you're livingВҰ49066\add*.\x + \xo 7:26-27: \xt Gen 9:4; Lev 17:10-14; 19:26; Deu 12:16,23; 15:23.\x*
\v 27 Any personВҰ49072 who does eatВҰ49075 bloodВҰ49078 must be cut off from \add вүҲthe community\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The priests' portions
\rem /s1 The Priests' Share; A Portion for the Priests
\p
\v 28 Then YahwehВҰ49086 told MoshehВҰ49089,
\v 29 вҖңTell the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ49095\add* that anyoneВҰ49098 who offers a peace offering to Yahweh must take \add вүҲsome of it as\add* his peace offering to Yahweh.
\v 30 They must \add вүҲpersonally carry\add* Yahweh's gift \add which will be\add* the breast with its fat and raise it \add вүҲin frontВҰ49129\add* of Yahweh as a wave offeringВҰ49115,
\v 31 and the priestВҰ49133 must burnВҰ49132 that fat up on the altarВҰ49137 \add вүҲbutВҰ49132\add* the breastВҰ49139 will be for AharonВҰ49140 and his sonsВҰ49141.
\v 32 The rightВҰ49145 thighВҰ49144 from the sacrificesВҰ49149 of your peaceВҰ49150 offeringsВҰ49150 must be given to the priestВҰ49148вҖ”
\v 33 whichever \add вүҲpriest (Aharon'sВҰ49161 descendant) who handled\add* the bloodВҰ49155 of the peaceВҰ49156 offeringsВҰ49152 andВҰ49157 the fat, that rightВҰ49165 thighВҰ49164 will be his portionВҰ49166
\v 34 because I took the breastВҰ49171 from the wave offering and the thighВҰ49175 from the contributionВҰ49176 of the \add вүҲIsraelis'\add* peaceВҰ49183 offerings, and I gaveВҰ49184 them to Aharon the priestВҰ49187 and his sons as an ongoing portionВҰ49189 from the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ49179 people\add*.
\v 35 That's the shareВҰ49197 for Aharon andВҰ49199 his sonsВҰ49200 from the gifts to Yahweh since Mosheh presentedВҰ49204 them to Yahweh as priestsВҰ49206.
\v 36 YahwehВҰ49211 commandedВҰ49210 them to be givenВҰ49212 to them \add back\add* on the dayВҰ49214 when he anointedВҰ49215 them out of all the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ49218 peopleВҰ49218\add* \add and made it\add* a permanent regulation for \add future\add* generationsВҰ49222.
\p
\v 37 \add #Those are the regulations\add* for the burntВҰ49226 \add #offerings\add*, the grainВҰ49227 \add #offerings\add*, the sinВҰ49228 \add #offerings\add*, the guiltВҰ49229 \add #offerings\add*, the ordinationВҰ49230 \add #offerings\add*, and the peaceВҰ49232 \add #offerings\add*
\v 38 that Yahweh \add вүҲgave to\add* MoshehВҰ49239 atВҰ49240 MtВҰ49240. Sinai onВҰ49240 the dayВҰ49242 when he orderedВҰ49235 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ49246\add* to presentВҰ49248 theirВҰ49251 offeringsВҰ49251 to Yahweh \add when they were there\add* inВҰ49240 the Sinai wildernessВҰ49253.
\c 8
\s1 The making priests to Aharon and of his child
\rem /s1 The Rites of Ordination; Ordination of the Priests; The priesthood; The Ordination of Aaron and His Sons
\r (Exo. 29:1-37)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ49258 told MoshehВҰ49261 \add (MosesВҰ49261)\add*,
\v 2 вҖңTake Aharon \add (AaronВҰ49267)\add* and his sonsВҰ49270 with their clothes and the anointingВҰ49276 oilВҰ49275, and the bullВҰ49279 for the sinВҰ49280 offeringВҰ49280 and twoВҰ49282 rams, and a basketВҰ49285 of unleavenedВҰ49286 breadВҰ49286,
\v 3 andВҰ49288 assembleВҰ49292 the entireВҰ49289 \add вүҲcommunity\add* at the entranceВҰ49295 to the \add вүҲsacredВҰ49296\add* tent.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ49299\add* MoshehВҰ49300 did exactly has YahwehВҰ49303 had commandedВҰ49302 him, andВҰ49305 the \add вүҲpeople\add* assembledВҰ49305 at the entranceВҰ49309 of the \add вүҲsacredВҰ49310\add* tent.
\v 5 ThenВҰ49313 MoshehВҰ49314 told the \add вүҲassembled people\add*, вҖңThis \add ceremony\add* is what YahwehВҰ49323 has told us to do.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ49326 MoshehВҰ49327 presentedВҰ49326 AharonВҰ49330 and his sonsВҰ49333 and \add after\add* washing them with waterВҰ49336,
\v 7 he put the tunicВҰ49342 on \add @Aharon\add* and wrapped the sashВҰ49345 \add around\add* him, and thenВҰ49338 put the robeВҰ49350 on him. ThenВҰ49338 he put the sacred apron on him, tying \add *its\add* finely woven waistband to fasten it onto him.
\v 8 ThenВҰ49364 he \add вүҲattached\add* the chest pouch and put the Urim and Tummim into the pouch.
\v 9 \add вүҲFinally\add* he placed the turban on his headВҰ49386, andВҰ49380 fastened the goldenВҰ49397 flower-shaped plateВҰ49396 (that sacredВҰ49399 crownВҰ49398 that demonstrates that Aharon is set apart to only serve Yahweh) to the frontВҰ49393 of the turban, exactly as Yahweh had instructedВҰ49401 MoshehВҰ49405.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ49407 MoshehВҰ49408 tookВҰ49407 the anointing oilВҰ49411 and anointed \add &Yahweh's\add* residence and everything in it, thus consecratingВҰ49424 \add вүҲit all\add*.
\v 11 Seven timesВҰ49433 he flicked some of it onto the altarвҖ”anointingВҰ49434 the altar and all its utensilsВҰ49442 and the basin and its base, thus consecrating them.
\v 12 He pouredВҰ49451 some of the anointing oilВҰ49452 over Aharon's headВҰ49455, thus anointing him to consecrate him.
\v 13 ThenВҰ49461 Mosheh presentedВҰ49461 Aharon's sonsВҰ49465 and dressed them in tunicsВҰ49468 and wrapped sashes around each of them, and tied their headbands onto them, just as YahwehВҰ49477 had instructedВҰ49476 Mosheh.
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ49482 he broughtВҰ49482 the bull for the sin offering, and AharonВҰ49487 and his sons placed theirВҰ49491 handsВҰ49491 on \add *its\add* head.
\v 15 Then \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:15 \ft It's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was still referring to Aharon here.\f* slaughtered it, and Mosheh took the blood and used his fingerВҰ49510 to put some on the \add four\add* \add вүҲprojecting corners\add* of the altar, thus purifying the altar. Then he pouredВҰ49518 \add the rest of\add* the blood out at the altar's base, sanctifying it \add вүҲso it could be used for making people right with God\add*.
\v 16 ThenВҰ49548 \add @Mosheh\add* tookВҰ49527 all the far thatВҰ49533 was on the innards and the lobe of the liverВҰ49539, and the twoВҰ49542 kidneysВҰ49543 and theirВҰ49546 fat, and \add *he\add* burnt them up on the altarВҰ49549.
\v 17 \add вүҲHowever,\add* he burnt up \add the rest of\add* the bullВҰ49553 \add вүҲincludingВҰ49554\add* its hide, fleshВҰ49559, andВҰ49551 dung, outsideВҰ49565 the camp, just as YahwehВҰ49569 had toldВҰ49568 \add *him\add*.
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ49574 \add @Mosheh\add* presentedВҰ49574 the ram for the burntВҰ49577 offeringВҰ49577, and Aharon and his sonsВҰ49580 placed theirВҰ49583 handsВҰ49583 on its headВҰ49586.
\v 19 ThenВҰ49589 \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:19 \ft It's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was still referring to Aharon here.\f* slaughtered it, andВҰ49590 Mosheh splashed the bloodВҰ49594 on \add вүҲeach side of\add* the altarВҰ49597.
\v 20 ThenВҰ49600 \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:20 \ft Again it's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was referring to Aharon (and possibly including his sons) here.\f* cut the ram into pieces, and Mosheh burnt up the headВҰ49609, and the pieces and the fat.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add ?@Aharon\add*\f + \fr 8:20 \ft Again it's not 100% clear from the Hebrew if the pronoun here refers to Aharon or to Mosheh, but as Mosheh's name is specifically mentioned in the next clause, we assume that вҖҳheвҖҷ was referring to Aharon here.\f* washedВҰ49623 the innards andВҰ49617 the legs, thenВҰ49617 Mosheh \add also\add* burnt \add *those\add* up on the altarВҰ49632 as a burnt offering that was pleasingВҰ49637 aromaВҰ49635 for Yahweh, just as Yahweh had \add вүҲinstructedВҰ49642\add* Mosheh.
